/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2709:Both `redeemFresh()` and `borrowFresh()` call `doTransferOut()` before writing the reduced cToken balance or increased borrow balance to storage. The reentrancy guard is local to this market instance only, so if the underlying token can trigger callbacks on transfer, the recipient can reenter a different market during the outbound transfer while this market's `getAccountSnapshot()` still reports stale collateral or debt.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2715:- Use a market whose underlying token can execute code during `transfer` to the borrower/redeemer.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2731:### F-003: Small `redeemUnderlying` calls can withdraw underlying while burning zero cTokens
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2735:When redeeming by underlying amount, `redeemFresh()` computes `redeemTokens = divScalarByExpTruncate(redeemAmountIn, exchangeRate)`. If rounding makes `redeemTokens == 0`, the function still proceeds: `redeemAllowed(..., 0)` is queried, `subUInt(accountTokens[redeemer], 0)` succeeds even for an address with no cTokens, and `doTransferOut()` sends `redeemAmountIn` underlying anyway.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2737:**Impact:** Any account can repeatedly drain small amounts of underlying from market cash without owning or burning cTokens. Each call is capped by the current zero-rounding threshold, but the attack is permissionless and repeatable.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2741:- Choose `redeemAmountIn` small enough that `redeemAmountIn / exchangeRate` truncates to zero cTokens.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2743:- Call `redeemUnderlying(redeemAmountIn)` from an address with zero cToken balance.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2745:- The contract transfers out the requested underlying while burning zero cTokens.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2754:/bin/bash -lc "rg -n \"ktaf|Thin-market donation inflation|f573E6740045b5387F6d36a26B102C2adF639af5|0xf5140fC35C6f94D02d7466f793fEB0216082d7E5|later deposits|donation inflation\" /Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124 /Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output -g '"'!**/foundry_validation/**'"'" in /Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/cases/ktaf/src
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2772:    "claim": "`exchangeRateStoredInternal()` prices shares from the contract's raw underlying balance via `getCashPrior()`, so direct token donations raise the exchange rate without minting any new cTokens. `mintFresh()` then floors `actualMintAmount / exchangeRate` and does not require `mintTokens > 0`, letting a thin-market attacker who already owns nearly all supply force later minters to receive too few, or even zero, cTokens.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2773:    "impact": "In an empty or very thin market, an attacker can seed a dust position, donate underlying to inflate the exchange rate, then front-run a victim mint so the victim donates assets for negligible or zero shares. The attacker can then redeem their cTokens against the victim's deposit, stealing most or all of it.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2775:      "Mint a dust amount into an empty or near-empty market so the attacker owns essentially all cTokens.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2776:      "Transfer underlying directly to the cToken contract, increasing `getCashPrior()` without increasing `totalSupply`.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2778:      "Redeem the attacker's cTokens to withdraw the donated cash plus the victim's deposit."
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2801:    "claim": "Both `redeemFresh()` and `borrowFresh()` call `doTransferOut()` before writing the reduced cToken balance or increased borrow balance to storage. The reentrancy guard is local to this market instance only, so if the underlying token can trigger callbacks on transfer, the recipient can reenter a different market during the outbound transfer while this market's `getAccountSnapshot()` still reports stale collateral or debt.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2804:      "Use a market whose underlying token can execute code during `transfer` to the borrower/redeemer.",
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2819:    "title": "Small `redeemUnderlying` calls can withdraw underlying while burning zero cTokens",
