/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/ktaf_p5_25_124/foundry_validation/F-001_Thin-market_donation_inflation_lets_an_a/codex_stderr_attempt4.log:2929:/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/inversefinance_p5_25_124/findings_acc.json:43:    "claim": "`mintFresh` computes `mintTokens = floor(actualMintAmount * 1e18 / exchangeRateMantissa)` and never checks that the result is nonzero. Since the exchange rate comes from raw market cash over `totalSupply`, and there is no minimum-liquidity or dead-shares defense, an attacker can mint a dust-sized initial position, donate underlying directly to the market, and raise the zero-mint threshold (`exchangeRateMantissa / 1e18`) high enough that later deposits are accepted while minting 0 cTokens.",
