eturn codes from `mint`, `redeem`, and `redeemUnderlying`. Stablecoin deposits update `stableCoinBalances` and user balances before proving that `mint` succeeded, withdrawals and interest sweeps assume redemptions succeeded as long as the external call did not revert, and a failed `mint` can leave a non-zero cToken allowance behind because `safeApprove` set it first and there is no path that resets it back to zero.","impact":"A non-reverting Compound-side failure can leave the pool in a silently inconsistent state: principal may sit idle in the staking contract while users are recorded as invested, redemptions can fail while accounting already assumes funds moved, unrelated idle balances may be consumed to satisfy withdrawals, and one failed `mint` can permanently DoS new deposits or the `getInterest()` re-mint path for that stablecoin because future `safeApprove` calls revert on the leftover allowance.","paths":["A stablecoin `deposit()` or `getInterest()` sets cToken allowance via `safeApprove()` and then calls `mint()`.","`mint()` returns a non-zero error code instead of reverting, so the transaction succeeds and the allowance may remain non-zero.","Internal staking balances already reflect the deposit or re-invest attempt even though Compound did not accept the funds.","A later deposit or re-mint attempt hits `safeApprove()` again and reverts because the old allowance was never reset to zero."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Skipped epochs and the hardcoded 2021 epoch start can brick dormant or never-before-used pools","locations":["Staking.sol:90","Staking.sol:91","Staking.sol:142","Staking.sol:145","Staking.sol:387","Staking.sol:466","Staking.sol:477"],"claim":"The constructor permanently hardcodes `epoch1Start = 1624230000` (June 21, 2021), while `deposit` and `withdraw` only attempt to initialize the current epoch. `manualEpochInit` then reverts unless `epochId - 1` is already initialized. 